South Africa’s NUM Union Rejects De Beers’ 7.5% Pay Offer, May Call Strike

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-07-20T10:55:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/south-africa-s-num-union-rejects-de-beers-7-5-pay-offer-may-call-strike.html
South Africa ’s National Union of
Mineworkers has rejected an offer from De Beers to raise
workers’ pay by 7.5 percent and the labor group has obtained a
government certificate allowing to proceed with a strike should
it choose, Peter Bailey, a negotiation for the union, said in an
interview today.  South Africa’s annual inflation rate is currently 5
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
